ED and Temp Processing Example

Setup: Load Functions

I’ve been encountering some difficultyrunning the routine with the functions from the package. I think it is still a good idea to run analyses from common functions (stored as their own scripts) rather than embedding the code of the functions into the scripts themselves (as in the earlier EP_temp_combine). I am recommending we try to load functions from the common files using source commands like this.

# set the working directory to work local
setwd("R:/heatProjections/")

# or through Rstudio in your browser 
# setwd("//mnt/projects/ohe/heatProjections/")
source("code/heatProjection/heatProjectR/R/filter_ed.R")
source("code/heatProjection/heatProjectR/R/get_prism.R")

filter_ed

Now try to run one of the functions using the test data. Note I changed the filter_ed function to take a file path, instead of a year and it defaults to the test data mapped locally.

test_path_ed <- "data/processed/ed_test_data.csv"
# real_path  <- "data/ED/cdph_ed_rln2005.csv"

out <- filter_ed(file_path = test_path_ed)
out
out

Using the test data allows us to quickly try out the other parameters of the function and make sure they are working.

out2 <- filter_ed(file_path = test_path_ed, numDiagnosis = 2)
out2 
out2

get_prism

Now try to run the get_prism function with the test data. Note I changed the filter_ed function to take a file path, instead of a year and it defaults to the test data mapped locally.

test_path_prism <- "data/processed/prism_test_data.csv"
# real_path  <- "data/PRISM/prism_2005.csv"

pris <- get_prism(file_path = test_path_prism)
# out <- filter_ed(file_path = real_path)

pris

combine_ed_temp

Lastly I made a new function that wraps the other two and combines their outputs. Notice the function write a file to the path of your choice and can retun the resulting table as a data table object.

source("code/heatProjection/heatProjectR/R/combine_ed_temp.R")

foo <- combine_ed_temp(file_path_ed = test_path_ed, file_path_prism = test_path_prism, output_path = "./data/processed/combined_test_data.csv")

foo
